body:
I went ahead and created a PR for this, and included the test.

The initial quick change (below) wasn't fully sufficient as there was some additional fallout (t_param_pattern.v)
```
                //} else if (origp && exprp->sameTree(origp)) {
                } else if (origp && ParameterizedHierBlocks::areSame(exprp, origp)) {
```

The issue on the regressing test was the struct width being not equal to the default width and then not correctly falling into this condition.  Added the sameTree() back in and then a logical or of the width compare anded with the added check above (ParameterizedHierBlocks::areSame().  This is then CI clean and I think covers the necessary cases.

```
                } else if (origp && (exprp->sameTree(origp)
                     || (exprp->num().width() == origp->num().width()
                         && ParameterizedHierBlocks::areSame(exprp, origp)))) {
```
